REFERENCE           EP1_SN_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Mired in greed and corruption, tangled in bureaucracy, the Galactic Republic is crumbling. In the outlying systems where the Trade Federation maintains a stranglehold on shipping routes, tensions are boiling over. With the crisis escalating, Supreme Chancellor Finis Valorum calls for an emergency trade summit. As humans and aliens gather, conspiracies sealed with large sums of money run rampant and no one is entirely above suspicion. But the greatest threat of all, remains unknown to everyone except three members of the Trade Federation who have entered into a shadowy alliance with a Dark Overlord, Darth Sidious. During the initial blockade of Trade Federation battleships around the Mid-Rim planet of Naboo, Supreme Chancellor Valorum sends two Jedi Knights, Master Qui-Gon Jinn and his Padawan, Obi-Wan Kenobi to negotiate with the Viceroy of the Trade Federation."

REFERENCE           EP1_EITD_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After rescuing Queen Amidala and her guards from the clutches of the Trade Federation in Theed, the Jedi escort the Queen off Naboo in her starship, in an attempt to reach the Republic capital world of Coruscant with news of the invasion. However, getting past the Trade Federation blockade proves very difficult and the Queen's ship is damaged in the escape. During the flee, repairs were made by R2-D2 but the ship didn't have enough power to reach Coruscant, so the group decide to land on Tatooine in the Outer Rim Territories, to refuel and repair the ship. Stranded on the desert planet, Jedi Master Qui-Gon Jinn discovers a 9-year old boy named Anakin Skywalker, a young slave unusually strong in the Force and a Midi-chlorian count surpassing that of even Grand Master Yoda. Anakin wins a thrilling Pod-Race and with it his freedom, as he leaves home to be trained as a Jedi. On the outskirts of Mos Espa, Qui-Gon and Anakin are approaching the Queen's starship, as they are ambushed by a dark-cloaked figure."

REFERENCE           EP1_DOTF_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Narrowly escaping Tatooine, the Jedi and Queen Amidala finally arrive on Coruscant. Qui-Gon, Obi-Wan and Anakin appear before the Jedi Council. Qui-Gon reports his encounter with his attacker, leaving the Council to consider that after a thousand years, the Sith have returned. Jedi Master Mace Windu questions Qui-Gon about the prophecy of the one who will bring balance to the Force, with Qui-Gon believing it to be young Anakin. Anakin takes a series of tests and although he shows Force-sensitivity, the Council deny him entry, citing his advanced age as the deciding factor. They order Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan to return to Naboo with the Queen, to discover the identity of their attacker. Upon their arrival on Naboo, Queen Amidala and the Jedi formulate a plan to capture the Viceroy and free the planet from Federation control. During the Battle for Naboo, the dark figure that attacked Qui-Gon on Tatooine, was waiting for them behind closed doors in the Palace hangar."

REFERENCE           EP2_AIL_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Around ten years have passed since the Battle of Naboo and Sheev Palpatine who was previously a Senator, is now the Supreme Chancellor of the Galactic Republic, after he was elected during the ongoing struggle for the control of Naboo. Young Anakin Skywalker, who is now nineteen years old, is showing promising signs of becoming a great Jedi Knight under his Master, Obi-Wan Kenobi, who vowed to keep his promise to his dying Master, Qui-Gon Jinn in the aftermath of the duel with the Sith Lord, Darth Maul. But as he'd grown, Anakin's exceptional skills had made the young Padawan brash and impulsive. Nevertheless, he idolized his Master. After returning from an adventure on the planet Glee Anselm, that was revealed to be a test for both Anakin and Obi-Wan, Anakin was later waiting for Obi-Wan in one of the Jedi Temple's training areas, where he gazed out across the horizon until his Master joined him for a sparring session."

REFERENCE           EP2_EJF_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Near the end of the Separatist Crisis, the Jedi Council have given Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi the task of discovering the identity of the Bounty Hunter responsible for the plot to assassinate Senator Amidala, the former Queen of Naboo. After recovering a toxic dart, Obi-Wan learns from his friend Dex that the dart belongs to the Cloners on Kamino, an Outer Rim planet that he discovers is strangely absent from the Jedi Archives. Obi-Wan then travels to the aquatic planet and upon arrival, is welcomed by the Kaminoan, Taun We. She takes Obi-Wan to the Kamino Prime Minister, who informs the Jedi Master about the creation of a Clone Army for the Republic and reveals that the original host is a Bounty Hunter named Jango Fett. Expressing an eagerness to meet this Bounty Hunter, Taun We directs a curious Obi-Wan to Jango's living quarters. After being greeted by a young Boba, and a calm but tension-filled discussion about Jango's recent whereabouts, Obi-Wan returns to his ship. Jango then tells Boba to pack his things and prepare to leave."

REFERENCE           EP2_TC_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After the two failed assassination attempts on Senator Amidala, young Padawan, Anakin Skywalker is assigned by the Jedi Council with protecting her, by escorting her back to her home planet of Naboo, where she will be in safer surroundings. Whilst there, Anakin discovers his love for her, but Padme is reluctant to express her feelings. During the night, Anakin continued to have vivid nightmares about his mother. Unable to let them go, he tells Padme that he has to leave Naboo and travel to Tatooine to find out if anything has happened to her. Padme says that she'll go with him. In order to begin his search after arriving on Tatooine, Anakin seeks out Watto. Watto tells him that a farmer named Cliegg Lars had freed and married Anakin's mother, Shmi. After finding the Lars Homestead, Cliegg explains to Anakin that Shmi has been abducted by Tusken Raiders and the attempted rescue had failed. Despite Cliegg's insistence that Shmi is already dead, Anakin refuses to give up hope and sets out to find the Tusken camp."

REFERENCE           EP2_PA_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "During the pursuit of the Bounty Hunter Jango Fett off of Kamino, Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi tracks him to the desert planet of Geonosis. Obi-Wan sneaks into a facility and witnesses a meeting of the Separatist Council, where it's revealed that the Viceroy of the Trade Federation was leading the plot to assassinate Senator Amidala. Obi-Wan reports back to the Jedi Council, but is ambushed by Droidekas and taken captive. After Obi-Wan's signal is rerouted to Senator Amidala's ship on Tatooine, Anakin and Padme travel to Geonosis to rescue him, but are captured in the Geonosian battle droid factory. Before being led out into the Arena for execution with Obi-Wan, Padme expresses her mutual feelings for Anakin. In the Arena, the three narrowly escape their executions, which involve an Acklay, a Nexu and a Reek. During the struggle, Grand Master Yoda arrives on Geonosis with the Clone Army, right behind a Jedi strike force led by Jedi Master Mace Windu, to save the captive Jedi and Senator."

REFERENCE           EP2_BOG_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After the rescue of the Jedi, the Droid and Clone armies battle one another in an intricate series of confrontations on a number of different fronts. Much of the Separatists' heavy equipment has already been loaded onto their transports, but with their communications being jammed, the rest is hastily thrown at the Clones in order to buy the Confederacy Navy enough time to escape. Meanwhile, the Republic army's goal is to capture the Separatists leadership and as much of the Geonosian droid founders intact as possible, in order to uncover the depths of the Separatist conspiracy. On all fronts, the two sides grapple with each other in fierce combat. Heavily-armored AT-TE walkers face down hordes of Battle droids, as spider droids sweep their laser cannons across Clone Trooper battalions. As the Trade Federation core ships attempt to take off, Grand Master Yoda commands the Clone's artillery to bring a number of them crashing to the ground."

REFERENCE           EP2_TCR_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "In the chaos of the battle between the battle droid army and the Grand Army of the Republic, the Separatist leader and renegade Jedi, Count Dooku, attempts to retreat to a private hangar where his starship is docked, using his Flitknot speeder. However, he is spotted by Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi, who directs the Republic Gunship carrying him, Anakin Skywalker, Padme and a small group of Clones to chase after the Count. Unfortunately, the Gunship is unable to shoot down the Count's speeder and Dooku's escorting Nantex-class starfighters slip-in behind it and open fire. One of their shots knocks Padme and a Clone Trooper out of the Gunship, but despite Anakin's protests and a heated disagreement with Obi-Wan, she is left behind. The Republic Gunship continues to pursue Count Dooku and eventually drops both Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker on to the landing platform of Dooku's hangar, shortly before being blasted out of the sky by laser fire."

REFERENCE           EP3_ROC_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Learning that Supreme Chancellor Palpatine has been kidnapped by General Grievous and the Separatists from the Republic capital of Coruscant, Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker along with his Master, Obi-Wan Kenobi return from the Outer-Rim Sieges in their Jedi Starfighters to thwart General Grievous' plot. To assist the Jedi Generals, Elite Clone Trooper pilots of Clone Flight Squad Seven, under the command of clone pilot CC-2237, otherwise known as "Oddball" join the rescue. The two Jedi fight their way through a swarm of Vulture and tri-fighter droid starfighters protecting the Invisible Hand, General Grievous' flagship. Anakin and Obi-Wan head for the ship, while the Clones distract the droids. After crash landing in the hangar, the two Jedi dispose of a small squad of droids, while R2-D2 locates the Supreme Chancellor. The only thing blocking their path is a stately former Jedi named Count Dooku, who is now the Sith Lord known as Darth Tyranus."

REFERENCE           EP3_EGG_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi and his apprentice, Anakin Skywalker deliver the Supreme Chancellor safely back to Coruscant, ending the separatist ploy. With Count Dooku now defeated, the Jedi Council doubles its efforts to bring General Grievous to justice. Anakin discreetly meets with his wife, Padme Amidala. Padme reveals to Anakin that she is pregnant and knowing that marriage was against the Jedi Order's rules, questions what they should do. A short while after, the Clone's Intelligence units track General Grievous to the Utapau system. The Jedi Council sends Obi-Wan after the Separatist leader, this time without the aid of Anakin. Already frustrated by the Council, Anakin is further dismayed to learn that Master Windu suspects Chancellor Palpatine is behind the perpetuation of the Clone Wars. The conflicted young Jedi is now stuck on Coruscant, faced with the growing divide between his friend and mentor, the Chancellor, and the Jedi Order, without the guidance of Obi-Wan, who begins his daring mission on Utapau."

REFERENCE           EP3_PO_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Not long after the Battle of Coruscant, Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker begins to see visions of his wife Padme, dying in childbirth. During a show at the Galaxies Opera House while they sit in the Chancellor's private box, Palpatine tells Anakin of a Sith Legend, "The Tragedy of Darth Plagueis the Wise", emphasizing that he had discovered a way to use the Dark Side to create life and cheat death. Anakin, desperate to prevent his prophetic visions from becoming real, questions Palpatine on how one might learn Plagueis' technique, but Palpatine simply tells him that it is impossible to learn it from a Jedi. Later, in the Chancellor's office, after Anakin tells Palpatine that Master Kenobi has engaged General Grievous, Palpatine finally reveals himself to be Darth Sidious. Prompting Anakin to take action, he goes to inform Jedi Master Mace Windu of Palpatine's true identity as a Sith Lord. In response, Mace Windu takes a squad of fellow Jedi Masters to arrest the Supreme Chancellor."

REFERENCE           EP3_JT_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Having made his choice in striking at Jedi Master Mace Windu, Anakin places all of his trust with Palpatine, who goes to work on the conflicted, young Jedi, playing on his fears and anxieties. The crafty Sith Lord manipulates Anakin into believing that the Jedi Order betrayed the Republic and him, and that Obi-Wan is equally complicit. Anakin swears his allegiance to Palpatine and to the Dark Side of the Force. Seduced by his newfound power, the newly christened Darth Vader is sent to the Jedi Temple on a quest to crush the traitorous Jedi threat, after the Chancellor declares the Jedi Order an enemy of the Galactic Republic. Joining him in the assault, the entire legion of the 501st Clone Troopers are transferred back to Coruscant to serve under Lord Vader. As Vader and the 501st initiate their attack, the Supreme Chancellor issues Order 66 to every Clone Trooper in the Republic. Around the galaxy, the Clones are ordered to mark all their Jedi Generals as traitors and eliminate them, beginning the Great Jedi Purge."

REFERENCE           EP3_AM_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "On Coruscant, the Jedi Order is broken and the Temple is in ruins. With no one left to oppose him, Darth Sidious is ready to declare the Clone Wars over and appoint himself Emperor of the galaxy. The only matter left to attend to is the remaining Separatist leaders, who are in hiding in the Mustafar System. Sidious dispatches Darth Vader to the volcanic world to end their lives with a final betrayal. Before travelling to Mustafar, Vader goes to see his pregnant wife Padme, to check if she and the baby are safe. Vader then tells Padme that the Jedi have tried to overthrow the Republic, and that he witnessed Jedi Master Mace Windu attempt to assassinate the Supreme Chancellor, himself. He then re-iterates his loyalties to the Chancellor, to the Senate and to Padme, and tells her that he has a very important mission to take care of in the Mustafar System, and asks Padme to wait for his return. Accompanied by R2-D2, Vader pilots his Jedi Starfighter and travels to Mustafar."

REFERENCE           EP3_RT_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Before leaving the Jedi Temple during Operation: Knightfall, the Sith Lord Darth Vader activated the beacon located in the Temple's central security station, signaling all remaining Jedi to return home to Coruscant and that the Clone Wars have ended, in the hopes that it would attract any remaining survivors of Order 66. Jedi Grand Master Yoda and Master Obi-Wan Kenobi, who managed to survive the first strike of the Jedi Purge on the Wookiee homeworld of Kashyyyk and Utapau, decide to regroup with assistance from Senator Bail Organa. Upon receiving the coded retreat message from the beacon, themselves and realising that it is a plot to lure others in to the trap and be killed, Grand Master Yoda and Master Obi-Wan both agree that there is too much at stake and decide to make their way back to Coruscant, with the intention of infiltrating the Jedi Temple's beacon hall and re-configuring the transmission."

REFERENCE           EP3_MOTF_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After Jedi Grand Master Yoda and Master Obi-Wan Kenobi re-calibrated the Temple beacon's code, now warning all remaining Jedi to go into hiding and stay away from the Temple, Obi-Wan tells Master Yoda that he wishes to know the truth of the events that had taken place. Despite Yoda's warning, he activates the Temple's security holo-footage on their way out, and they discover that Anakin, Obi-Wan's now-former apprentice had led the assault. Knowing they must destroy the Sith Lords for the sake of the galaxy, they decide to split-up and take out the two Sith individually. Obi-Wan pleads with Master Yoda to send him to face the Emperor, unable to bear the thought of striking down his former friend and student, but Yoda points out that Darth Sidious is far too strong for Obi-Wan, and instead sends him to track down Darth Vader. Meanwhile, Grand Master Yoda infiltrates the Senate building, determined to kill the recently anointed Galactic Emperor."

REFERENCE           EP3_BOTH_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After being tasked with searching for Darth Vader while Master Yoda confronts the new Galactic Emperor, Obi-Wan is lost for where to begin his search for his former apprentice. So he seeks out Padme, in the hope that she will lead him to her husband. Obi-Wan then subtly breaks the unthinkable news to Padme that Anakin has turned to the Dark Side, after revealing that he saw a security hologram of Anakin killing younglings. Obi-Wan continues to explain the chain of events of how the Chancellor is behind everything, including the Clone War and Anakin becoming Palpatine's new apprentice. Obi-Wan re-iterates to Padme that he must find Anakin, but Padme refuses to disclose her husband's location. As Obi-Wan leaves, he turns to question Padme about Anakin being the father of her unborn baby. Feeling distressed, Padme travels to Mustafar in search of her husband, unaware that Obi-Wan has snuck and hidden aboard her starship before take-off."

REFERENCE           EP4_AOTTIV_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "0 BBY, 19 years after the formation of the Galactic Empire and the Imperial grip on the galaxy is now complete. On the remote, tropical planet of Scarif in the Outer Rim Territories, where the Imperial Citadel databanks are located, a small band of Rebels under the improvised call sign of "Rogue One" have just narrowly managed to extract the plans for the Galactic Empire's newly constructed battle station, the Death Star. The assault comes at great cost, as Governor Tarkin arrives with the Death Star and fires a single reactor ignition of the superlaser to destroy the compromised base. After paying respects to his fallen comrades, Admiral Raddus orders his fleet to jump to hyperspace, but before the entire fleet can escape, most are intercepted by Darth Vader's Star Destroyer, the Devastator. In pursuit of the Death Star plans, Lord Vader boards Raddus' disabled command ship and singlehandedly massacres hallways of Rebel troops, only to watch as the Tantive IV launches from the hangar bay and narrowly escapes with them."

REFERENCE           EP4_OLS_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "As the Millennium Falcon is forced to land in Bay 327, Han Solo prompts everyone to hide in the ship's sensor-proof smuggling compartments, to trick the Imperials into thinking they have abandoned the ship. As the Imperial Scouts get off the ship, Kenobi tells Han that he will take care of the tractor beam, which prompts Han to call him a "damn fool". Soon enough, with Luke Skywalker and Han both disguised as Stormtroopers, they take control of the hangar's control room, where Obi-Wan learns the location of a terminal that if it's power is cut, would allow the ship to leave. He decides to go alone despite Luke's protest, to whom he tells that his destiny lay on a different path than his own, and reassured him that the Force would be with him always. As Luke, Han and Chewbacca learn of Princess Leia's presence on the station and set out to rescue her, Obi-Wan manages to disable the tractor beam. However, as he makes his way back to the Falcon, he comes face to face with his former apprentice, Darth Vader."

REFERENCE           EP5_TOAJ_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After escaping the icy battle on Hoth, Luke Skywalker follows the guidance of Obi-Wan Kenobi's spirit to a remote swamp world called Dagobah. Shrouded in mist and teeming with life, the planet hides secrets of the old Jedi Order. Guided by the Force, Luke locates the humble dwelling of an eccentric old creature who soon reveals himself as Master Yoda, the Jedi Grand Master long thought lost. Though skeptical of Luke's readiness, Yoda reluctantly agrees to train him in the ways of the Force. Luke begins an arduous routine of physical drills, mental discipline, and deep meditation, struggling to balance his impatience with Yoda's insistence on serenity. As his training intensifies, Luke senses the lingering shadow of the dark side and the dangers it poses - not only to himself, but to his friends. Yoda warns him that fear and anger are powerful paths to darkness, and that failure to control them will doom him. It is here, among the vines and shadows of Dagobah, that Luke faces his greatest test yet."

REFERENCE           EP5_DWTDL_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After Han Solo is captured and delivered to Cloud City under Imperial control, Luke Skywalker sets out alone to rescue his friends. Ignoring Yoda's warning that he is not ready, Luke lands his X-wing on the gleaming city in the clouds, unaware that Darth Vader lies in wait. Guided by his connection to the Force, Luke moves cautiously through the silent corridors until he reaches the carbon-freezing chamber. The dim light of the chamber cuts through the steam rising from the machinery as a familiar sound fills the air - the ignition of a crimson blade. Vader steps from the shadows, calm and imposing, and ignites his lightsaber. Luke answers with his own, the hum of their weapons echoing through the chamber as the duel begins. The clash of blue and red marks the start of a battle that will change Luke's destiny forever."

REFERENCE           EP6_TGPOC_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Years prior to the Battle of Yavin, the vile gangster Jabba the Hutt hired Han Solo to smuggle spice for him. However, on one spice run, Han was boarded by Imperial forces and forced to jettison the spice to avoid incrimination. After Han was unable to repay Jabba, he placed a bounty on his head. Several years after the initial bounty, Han was tracked to Cloud City on Bespin by the feared bounty hunter Boba Fett. There, Solo was captured, tortured and frozen in carbonite by Darth Vader, after which he was turned over to Boba Fett for delivery to the Hutt crime lord. Across the Jundland Wastes on Tatooine, Luke Skywalker was leading a campaign to rescue his captive friend from Jabba the Hutt. Following a failed infiltration of the Hutt's palace, Jabba attempts to execute Luke, Han and his companion Chewbacca on the Dune Sea, by throwing them into the Great Pit of Carkoon, home of the Sarlacc. Luke was prepared for this type of situation, having stored his lightsaber inside of his droid R2-D2, prior to the rescue attempt."

REFERENCE           EP6_FAS_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "After the Rebel strike team lands on Endor and prevents Imperial scout troopers from reporting their presence in a speeder bike chase, Luke, Han and Chewbacca fall into a booby-trap set by the Ewoks. Convinced of the Rebels' good intentions, the Ewoks set them free and that evening make them a "part of the tribe", thereby agreeing to join the fight against the Empire. But Luke decides the time has come for him to leave and face Darth Vader in the hope of turning him back to the Light Side. Leia follows Luke out of the tribal gathering, where he tells her that Vader is his father and she is his sister. Leia is rendered utterly shocked, but accepts the truth. Vader arrives in his shuttle on a docking bay, and Luke, having already surrendered to the Empire, talks alone with Vader in an attempt to bring the Sith Lord out of the Dark Side of the Force, but to no avail. The Empire takes Luke into custody for transportation to the Death Star. The next day, the Rebel fleet enters hyperspace from Sullust to prepare for the final attack. Luke and Vader finally enter the Death Star and confront the Emperor."

REFERENCE           EP7_ACC_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "With the Starkiller Base shields down, two Resistance Squadrons led by Poe Dameron commence their assault. Seeing this, Han Solo, Chewbacca, Finn and Rey try to create an opening by planting thermal detonators inside the base. Sensing his father's presence, Kylo goes to meet Han. Han calls out to him by his birth name "Ben", and they approach each other on a bridge over a large pit. Han pleads with his son to reject Snoke and return to the light side of the Force. Ben, removing his mask and appearing regretful, holds out his lightsaber to Han, asking for his father's help. Han tries to retract the lightsaber from Ben's hand, but he resists. Ben ignites the weapon through Han's torso, as Han strokes his son's face for the last time, before falling to his death. Enraged, Chewbacca, Rey and Finn start firing at Ren and the stormtroopers. Back on D'Qar, Leia feels Han die through the Force, squeezing her eyes shut against the tears. Chewbacca injures Ren with his bowcaster, but Ren chases them out of the base and catches up to Finn and Rey in the forest."

REFERENCE           EP8_SF_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Captured by the First Order and brought aboard the Supremacy, Rey is escorted into a massive throne room bathed in crimson light. There, she comes face to face with Supreme Leader Snoke, the dark figure who has haunted her visions and manipulated events from the shadows. Around them, Praetorian Guards stand ready, their armor gleaming like blood. Snoke taunts Rey, revealing that her connection with Kylo Ren was no accident - it was his design, a trap to lure her into his grasp. Bound by the Force and stripped of her lightsaber, Rey resists Snoke's attempts to break her spirit. As the Supremacy shudders under distant bombardment, Snoke commands Kylo Ren to fulfill his destiny. The air thickens with tension as Rey realizes that her fate, and the fate of the Resistance, hangs in the balance."

REFERENCE           EP8_FT_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "On Crait, the surviving Resistance fighters regroup at the abandoned Rebel base. General Organa orders her forces to shut the shield door. Poe and Leia send a distress signal to their allies in the Outer Rim Territories, seeking help. Shortly after, they sense the earth shaking while the vulptices scurry away. They realize that the First Order has arrived with a phalanx of AT-AT, AT-M6 walkers and a superlaser siege cannon. As the superlaser burns through the gate of the Crait base, Kylo Ren orders his forces to storm the base. Connix informs D'Acy that the Resistance broadcast has reached multiple points but that they have received no response. Leia laments that the galaxy has lost hope. However, Luke suddenly arrives to comfort Leia. After exchanging pleasantries, Luke apologizes and tells Leia that he has come to confront Ren. Leia thinks her son is gone, but Luke reassures her that nobody is ever really gone. After handing Han's lucky dice to Leia, Luke walks out through the gate to confront Kylo Ren and the First Order, while C-3PO and the rest of the Resistance look on."

REFERENCE           REBELS_TFOAJ_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Seeking answers within the ancient Jedi Temple on Lothal, Kanan Jarrus enters a meditative state and is transported into a surreal vision. The grand halls of the temple stretch endlessly before him, illuminated by an eerie glow. Suddenly, figures emerge from the shadows - Jedi Temple Guards wielding blazing yellow lightsabers. Silent and imposing, they move toward him with purpose, their voices echoing accusations of failure and weakness. Kanan ignites his blade, ready to defend himself, but the guardians' relentless strikes force him deeper into the vision. Each blow tests not his strength, but his conviction as a Jedi and as a teacher to Ezra. With no way out but forward, Kanan prepares for a trial that will determine his true path."

REFERENCE           REBELS_TS_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "It is 2 BBY, 17 years after the end of the Clone Wars, and the former Sith Lord now simply known as Maul, is lost on the desert world of Tatooine, on his burning quest for vengeance against his long-time enemy, Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi. In exasperation and rage, Maul cries out Kenobi's name. He does not wish to die in the desert and vows to draw the old Jedi Master out of hiding. Suddenly, Maul has an idea, slowly opening his hand to reveal a fragment of the Sith holocron. At Chopper Base, Ezra Bridger is woken by a feint recording of Obi-Wan's voice, tracing it to Kanan Jarrus' Jedi holocron. He then hears Maul roaring Kenobi's name again, from the red Sith holocron. Believing that Obi-Wan is alive and could help the Rebellion, Ezra travels to Tatooine, fearing that Maul is closing in on the Jedi Master. Upon searching the plains, in the blazing heat, Ezra succumbs to exhaustion and heat stroke, as he is approached by a shrouded figure."

REFERENCE           REBELS_LOD_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Lost within the enigmatic World Between Worlds, Ahsoka Tano steps across shimmering pathways suspended in an endless void. Voices from the past echo through the infinite expanse, fragments of moments she once lived - and others she never knew. Then, from the darkness, a familiar presence emerges, Anakin Skywalker. But his face carries the mark of corruption, his eyes burning with a Sith's fury. Without a word, Anakin ignites his lightsaber, and Ahsoka finds herself forced into a battle she never wanted. Steel meets fire as their blades clash across the spectral bridges, every strike pulling Ahsoka deeper into a storm of memory and pain. Around them, the gateways ripple and distort as time itself bends under the weight of their confrontation."

REFERENCE           ROTE_AOE_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Darth Maul, with his replacement bionic legs attached to his upper torso, seeks out the Lars Homestead to find and avenge himself upon Obi-Wan Kenobi. Upon his arrival, he is met by Owen Lars, whom he swiftly disarms. Beru screams, but it is not until Maul threatens the infant Luke in her arms that Kenobi finally reveals himself, asking whether Palpatine knows he is still alive. Maul replies that he neither knows, nor cares about his former master, or even about the ancient feud between Jedi and Sith. Maul claims to have been tracking Kenobi for years, just missing him on his missions to Kamino, Geonosis, and Mustafar, and to have killed many witnesses on Polis Massa before finally gaining crucial information in Mos Espa from an aged Toydarian junk dealer, whom he then murdered. Maul gloats that he knew threatening Luke would bring his old adversary out into the open."

REFERENCE           ROTE_DVR_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "When Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker fell, both to the pull of the Dark Side, and to the blade of his former Master Obi-Wan Kenobi, he rose back up. Full of hatred, revenge, and more machine than man. Having lost everything that was once dear to him, the former Jedi must take his first steps into a darker world, as Darth Vader, Dark Lord of the Sith! A short time after his loss to Obi-Wan Kenobi, Vader returns to Mustafar, where the blueprints for his new stronghold had been created by Colonel Brenne, as a reward from his master, Darth Sidious. Back onboard the Executor, Vader's personal flagship in his private Meditation Chamber, the Sith Lord must face and exorcise the haunting inner demons from his past that have psychologically tormented and afflicted him, in order to fully become the the ruthless Sith Lord and scourge of the galaxy that the Emperor has moulded and created."

REFERENCE           TFU_SLT_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Under the command of the Sith Lord Darth Vader, a large military force is deployed to Kashyyyk. During the battle, Vader defeats Kento Marek in a lightsaber duel and discovered the exiled Jedi's son. Impressed by his potential in the Force, the Sith Lord abducted the young infant, shortly after he killed the boy's father and a squad of Imperials, in order to keep Galen's existence a secret. Concealed on-board Vader's incomplete flagship, the Executor, and assigned the codename "Starkiller", the apprentice repressed all memories of his previous life, and spent the next two decades training as a Sith under Darth Vader's supervision, with the ultimate goal of standing at Vader's side against the Emperor. Starkiller takes on the role of Vader's personal assassin and enforcer, dispatching problematic individuals throughout the Imperial military with vicious enthusiasm. Starkiller personally developed into a staunch Imperialist, viewing these assassinations as a form of service to the Empire."

REFERENCE           TFU_FH_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "General Kota was unimpressed by Starkiller's victory, feeling that it didn't even begin to dent Palpatine's "infinite" army. However, after Starkiller appealed to his warrior sense of honor, Kota agrees to join him, revealing that he has a contact in the Imperial Senate who could use Starkiller's lightsaber, due to his eagerness to kill Stormtroopers. Shortly after rescuing Kota, Starkiller begins feeling drawn to the Jedi Temple, thus causing him to return to Coruscant for a third time. Upon his return, however, Starkiller finds the Jedi Temple guarded by many stormtroopers and several variations. Despite being overwhelmingly outnumbered, the apprentice single-handedly kills numerous Imperials as he infiltrates the ruins of the Temple. When he reached the chamber of the former Jedi High Council, he witnesses a Force induced vision of his master, the Sith Lord Darth Vader, engaged in combat with a Jedi unknown to him. But just as Starkiller had defeated the Jedi in defense of Vader, he realized that it was a vision of his dead father."

REFERENCE           TFU_RTR_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Rejecting the codename "Starkiller", Darth Vader's former apprentice reclaims his birth name Galen Marek and for the first time, considers himself as a Jedi. Opting to save the Rebel Alliance by tracking down both Vader and the Senators, Galen enters into a deep meditation and discovers the location of the Rebels on the incomplete Death Star. Travelling to the Horuz system, he uses the Rogue Shadow's cloaking device to approach the massive battle station. Standing on the boarding ramp of the ship, Galen and Juno exchange their last words. When Juno inquires as to whether or not he would survive, Galen answers that he would most likely die in the attempted rescue. Bidding farewell to Juno, he leaps into the Death Star's extensive superstructure. After following one of the superlaser tubes, Galen reaches a convergence chamber. He then uses the Force to de-activate the locking mechanism, and gains access through the massive door that leads in to the Emperor's Observation Dome."

REFERENCE           TFU_AFH_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "The Emperor's Sith Assassin, Starkiller and his Imperials captured the Tantive IV and Princess Leia Organa. Leia was taken prisoner and the Tantive was destroyed. Starkiller then traveled to Tatooine disguised as a Tusken Raider to locate the stolen Death Star plans suspected to be with two droids. His master contacted him to ask Jabba the Hutt of any information on the droids. Jabba said he knew nothing, but a blunder by his translator droid revealed the droids to be at Docking Bay 94 in Mos Eisley. Furious, Jabba dropped Starkiller into the Rancor pit as the Sith Lord realized his treachery. Starkiller battled Jabba's rancor and eventually killed it. Jabba then enraged calls his guards to kill him and even puts a bounty on his head. Starkiller left on a desert skiff and made his way to Docking Bay 94, where he saw the droids with Luke Skywalker escaping aboard the Millennium Falcon. As he attempted to pursue them, Obi-Wan Kenobi remained to face Starkiller, who was thrilled at the prospect of being able to kill the legendary Jedi Master."

REFERENCE           TFU_WOTE_DESC
LANG_ENGLISH        "Igniting his lightsaber, Galen Marek was ready to strike down his mentor, General Rahm Kota, but instead he turned and swung at the Emperor. Admitting to having foreseen the attack, Palpatine shocked him with a blast of Force lightning before flinging him through a window out onto the landing platform, as Juno flew the Rogue Shadow down for boarding. Galen later woke-up on an operating table in the EmPal SuRecon Center, much like the one that Darth Vader's transformation took place on, while his suit was being constructed. He was now wearing his own suit of armor, presumably the only thing keeping him alive. Becoming the Emperor's new apprentice and known as Lord Starkiller, he is obliged to do Palpatine's bidding just as Vader before him. During the Battle of Hoth, Lord Starkiller infiltrates the Rebel's Echo Base through a series of unstable ice caverns. Fighting his way through the base, Starkiller eventually gets into a confrontation with Luke Skywalker."

ENDMARKER